claim.claim-text:
1. An event sensor device, comprising:
a pulse generator that responds to detection of an event by generating a voltage pulse having a pulse amplitude and pulse width;
a printed voltage dividing circuit that receives said voltage pulse and generates, responsive to said pulse amplitude and said pulse width, a display driving signal, said printed voltage dividing circuit comprising a plurality of individual threshold devices; and
a graduated-scale display responsive to said display driving signal which produces an indication of said detection of an event by way of said display driving signal, said graduated-scale display comprising a plurality of individually addressable display elements;
each said threshold device connected to a unique one of said individually addressable display elements for driving said connected individually addressable display element in response to said detection of an event by way of said display driving signal.
